<component id="slide02">
<text><![CDATA[<font size="14"><b><ul><li>Generic routing encapsulation (GRE) is a tunneling protocol that is used to create a point-to-point link to Cisco routers.</li><br/><li>GRE supports multiprotocol tunneling, including IP.</li><br/><li>GRE can be used in combination with IPsec.</li></ul></b></font>]]></text>
</component>





