<component id="slide03">
<text><![CDATA[<font size="14"><b><ul><li>IPsec is a framework of open standards that establishes the rules for secure communications.</li><br/><li>IPsec relies on existing algorithms to achieve  encryption, authentication, and key exchange.</li><br/><li>IPsec can encapsulate a packet using either Authentication Header (AH) or the more secure Encapsulation Security Protocol (ESP).</li><br/><li>IPsec uses the Internet Key Exchange (IKE) protocol to establish the key exchange process.</li></ul></b></font>]]></text>
</component>






