<component id="slide04">
<text><![CDATA[<font size="14"><b><ul><li>The first task in creating a site-to-site VPN is to ensure that the existing ACLs on perimeter routers, firewalls, or other routers do not block IPsec traffic.</li><br/><li>The second task is to define the parameters within the IKE policy, which are used during negotiation to establish ISAKMP peering.</li><br/><li>The third task is to define the IPsec transform set, which consists of a combination of an AH transform, an ESP transform, and the IPsec mode.</li><br/><li>The fourth task is to configure the crypto ACL to define which traffic is protected through the IPsec tunnel.</li><br/><li>The final task is to create and apply a crypto map that specifies the parameters of the IPsec SAs.</li></ul></b></font>]]></text>
</component>



